But before we dive into the code, let's have a little chat: Are you sure you want to make a script so efficient? Imagine a PDF full of love letters from Molière to his muse, and now it's just numbers and dates! *sniff* 

Okay, back to business. Here's a playful and short Perl script to get you started:

```perl
#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use PDF::API2;
use PDF::Text::API;

# Open a PDF file
my $pdf = PDF::API2->open("path_to_your_pdf_file.pdf");

# Extract text from the PDF
my $page = $pdf->open_page(1);  # Open the first page
my $text = $page->text;

# Search for specific text or data (e.g., date, author, table information)
if ($text =~ /date: (\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2})/) {
    print "The date is: $1\n";
}
elsif ($text =~ /author: (\w+)/) {
    print "The author is: $1\n";
}
# Add more regex patterns to extract more information

# Enjoy your newly extracted data!
```

